[http://p2pdl.cs.odu.edu/index.html FreeLib] is a project of Old Dominion University and headed by professors, Dr. Kurt Maly and Dr. Mohammad Zubair.  This is a relatively new project (August 2005) and currently offers only a detailed proposal and a beta Freelib version 1.0 (untested).  Funding for the project was provided by the US National Science Foundation.

== FreeLib - Peer to Peer Digital Library Project ==


In the Peer-to-Peer Digital library project, we apply pure peer-to-peer techniques in the context of digital library to achieve self-sustainability, scalability, and to evolve communities of common interest. The evolution of communities is a key feature in the system and is based on analyzing the access patterns among nodes. The system has rich metadata-based search and publishing services. Every node in the system indexes a small collection, however, with the large scale of a peer-to-peer system, tremendous collection sizes are possible. 


